Strategy<br>
--------<br>
There are several roles that must be filled for the group to work:<br>
<br>
1.Puller/tank<br>
-----------<br>
This is ideally someone who can pull 4 to 8 MOBs without dying.<br>
<br>
a. Bard<br>
-work well due to Rune song absorbing some damage<br>
-Mana/Heal song to reduce downtime<br>
<br>
b. Monk/Warrior/SK/Paladin<br>
-lots of HP to pull MOBs<br>
-emergency tanking/taunting if needed<br>
<br>
2. Healer<br>
------<br>
Cleric is the only choice here, loaded with the quickest heal possible,<br>
group heals, Celestial Healing and Rez.  Unfortunately shaman/druid cannot<br>
cast heals fast enough to work well.<br>
<br>
3. Stunner<br>
----------<br>
Enchanter is the only choice here for the area effect stun spells.<br>
<br>
4. Evac Nuker<br>
----------<br>
At least 1 nuker should have evac loaded, when pulls go bad or adds force<br>
people to go OOM, this person should always save mana for an evac when leader<br>
calls it.  If this person goes OOM during a fight, they are not doing their job.<br>
They nuke, but must have enough to get people out ASAP. This is either a druid<br>
or a wizard.<br>
<br>
5. Nuker<br>
----------<br>
This is a wizard or a mage.  Purely for point blank area effect damage spell.<br>
Mage also brings an earth pet which can be useful for tanking.<br>
<br>
6. Nuker/Backup stunner<br>
-----------------------<br>
Wizards have area effect spells that also stun.  Another enchanter here can cycle<br>
stunning and using Gravity Flux for damage and Blanket of Forgetfulness for mem blur.<br>
<br>
<br>
Examples<br>
--------<br>
Lets take some groups and define their role based on class:<br>
1. Bard - puller, group damage absorption, tanking<br>
2. Cleric - healing/buffing<br>
3. Enchanter - cycle all 4 color spells, mez as needed<br>
4. Wizard - damage<br>
5. Mage - damage, pet tanking<br>
6. Druid - evac, damage shield, backing healer/regen/buff, damage<br>
<br>
1. Warrior - puller, tanking, taunting<br>
2. Cleric - healing/buffing<br>
3. Enchanter - cycle all 4 color spells, mez as needed<br>
4. Wizard - damage<br>
5. Mage - damage, damage shield, pet tanking<br>
6. Wizard - evac, damage<br>
<br>
1. Shadowknight - puller, tanking, taunting<br>
2. Cleric - healing/buffing<br>
3. Enchanter - cycle all 4 color spells<br>
4. Wizard - damage<br>
5. Wizard - evac, damage<br>
6. Enchanter - mez/mem blur, stun, damage<br>
<br>
<br>
What to do?<br>
-----------<br>
Assuming the first group in the above list, in Old Sebilis as an example.<br>
<br>
The object of an AOE group is to pull a train, everything you know about<br>
pulling safely is thrown out here.<br>
<br>
1. Set up, buff everyone with resolution or heroic bond, symbol, etc.<br>
2. Rune the puller (casters may use self only damage absorption)<br>
3. Med to full (clarity/clarity2 and mana song help a lot)<br>
4. Puller runs out and gets a bunch of MOBs<br>
   (avoid high HP mobs, frogs are great, beetles and golems are tough, use your judgement)<br>
5. Train comes, the enchanter (the stunner) starts stunning the frogs until they all arrive<br>
6. Group lead will shout NUKE<br>
7. All casters move in the middle of the frogs and start casting their point blank area effect spells<br>
8. The stunner does NOT stop casting area effect stuns until everything is dead<br>
  - due to recast delays, all 4 stuns need to be cycled<br>
9. Cleric either heals individuals, or does group heal<br>
  - casters do not have too many hitpoints and low AC, cleric should account for that<br>
  - casters are not tanks, their hitpoints may drop fast, when in doubt do a quick heal<br>
  - if people are getting hit, start casting group heal<br>
  - use your judgment and keep people alive<br>
A. Any adds are added to the stun/nuke area<br>
B. If one or two frogs remain, switch to direct damage and let the pet/puller tank<br>
<br>
If nukers are out of mana and more than 1 frog is left, it is up to the group leader to decide if<br>
an evac is called, if pet should tank, or if they should be mezzed until mana returns. This should<br>
be rare in a good AOE group.<br>
<br>
Strange situations arise from broken rooms, where spawn time is staggered.  Here you mez and wait for<br>
all to pop in, keep all of them mezzed close to each other.  Then pull a few more and repeat.<br>
<br>
There are many variations, but the idea remains the same.  Keep them stunned while you area nuke.<br>
<br>
You may get a cleric who will get bored in a good group, since everything is stunned and dying, people<br>
should not be getting very hurt.  If the cleric has surplus mana, let them throw in an area effect damage<br>
spell :) <br>
<br>
Also, always make sure the evacer knows that they have to have enough mana to do emergency evac.  Only time<br>
they may use that mana is to finish off the last MOB and be sure it is safe.  Evacer should also have a<br>
Modulation Rod for emergency mana, as should the cleric. Others should have Modulation Rods, but they are<br>
not required.<br>
<br>
Have fun...and good luck.<br>
<br>
