he method we use does not require a tank.  Infact, we don't use tanks and we don't pull the mobs to us.... we go to the mobs in essence.<br>
<br>
Our guild has a weekly AoE group that gets together every Fri night.  The usual group consists of:<br>
<br>
Enchanter<br>
Bard<br>
Cleric<br>
Wizard<br>
Wizard<br>
Wizard<br>
<br>
There are nights when there will be 1-2 of these people missing.  Fortunately, when that occurs others of us from the guild fill the spots.  When I go, the group looks like:<br>
<br>
Enchanter<br>
Bard<br>
Cleric<br>
Wizard<br>
Wizard<br>
Mage (me)<br>
<br>
An example of what we do:<br>
<br>
First and biggest of priorities is for everyone to know EXACTLY where to go, where to stop, and to stay right ontop of the enc.  Say, we're going to rush from outside D1 to Pickler... Everyone starts running at the same time, Enc and myself head straight to pickler, one other groupie grabs iksar necro room, another grabs library on the way in... meanwhile myself, cleric, and enc rush straight to pickler, enc starts stunning, and I immediately start aoe'ing incase enc has any resists... so they'll agro on me instead of enc.<br>
<br>
I do not know all the minute details as to what each different class uses spell wise.  I do know that the cleric doesn't use complete heals... he sticks with the smaller, fast casting heals.  The enc has 3 stuns loaded, wizzies have 3 pbaoe's, I have scintillation, etc.<br>
<br>
Avg exp on a trip like this for me while I was level 53 was 1/2 a blue bub per &quot;pull&quot;.. or run rather.  Our average number of mobs per run was around 12-20'ish.<br>
<br>
