<br>
1) It's easier to grab a large space to AE.<br>
2) It's just as easy to do as in sebilis!<br>
<br>
What I'd suggest before you decide to use the following strategy is spend some time in charasis getting aquainted with the zone layout. You want everyone in the group to have a good feel of how the zone is layed out before you try this.<br>
<br>
Now, once your group feels ready to run around HS with multiple mobs on your tail, here's what you do:<br>
<br>
Cleric has DA/DB up.<br>
Enchanter has stuns up.<br>
4 other PB Nukers have PB nukes up. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
You designate ONE spot for you to drop the bombs at and the cleric has to know where they are going at a bare minimum. It is best if you chose a corner as it is considerably easier to pack the mobs in together so that your AE's will hit them all.<br>
<br>
Have the cleric pop DA and start running for ground zero. Wait approximately 4 seconds before you follow around behind them, giving enough time for all the mobs between your position and ground zero to aggro on the DA cleric and HT the cleric, while DA soaks up the harm touches. When your group arrives you start unloading the PBs and nuke everything, and you didn't even have to worry about the harm touches! Bonus points for magicians who bring extra mobs with their pets!<br>
<br>
My only gripe with Magicians in AE groups is that Dyzil's Deafening Decoy seems to be the perfect pet for these groups, but doesn't cast it's damage shield often enough and doesn't proc very often either. <br>
<br>
P.S. Lemme know if you need another person for your AE groups Teldiva! I love AE. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Leguin Garamonde<BR>
